      "side": 1,
      "message": "Replaced with:\n\n```java\n  this.moduleJar \u003d sitePaths.lib_dir.resolve(\"cache-chroniclemap.jar\");\n```\n\nCaveat: this hard-codes the artifact name. If the JAR is renamed (e.g. `cache-chroniclemap-libmodule.jar`), `CompilerUtils.addClassPath` returns false and the libModule fails fast at boot with IllegalStateException (\"Failed to register libModule JAR with chronicle compiler: ...\"), so the misconfiguration is loud rather than silent.",
