      "side": 1,
      "message": "Test wiring required adjustment.\n\nThree ITs construct the module directly (new ChronicleMapCacheModule() in createModule() / inside a configure() block), bypassing Guice. They now pass a throwaway new SitePaths(Paths.get(\"/tmp\")) wrapped in try/catch (SitePaths\u0027 constructor declares throws IOException).\n\nTo keep this safe, configure() skips addClassPath registration when the derived JAR path doesn\u0027t exist — in tests the libModule is on the test classpath anyway, so the workaround isn\u0027t needed there.\n\nHappy to revert to the original getCodeSource() lookup if you\u0027d prefer to avoid the hardcoded filename + test-side try/catch — that variant is one self-contained block in one file with no caller fanout. Just let me know.",
