      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yes, I think that the code was more robust and there was less boiler plate when were deriving it from the loaded class instead of hardcoding the jar name.\n\nPerhaps having a small named helper function would help making this obvious?\nsomething like:\n\n```\nprivate static String moduleJarPath() {\n    return ChronicleMapCacheModule.class.getProtectionDomain().getCodeSource().getLocation().getPath();\n  }\n```\n\nand then:\n\n```\nCompilerUtils.addClassPath(moduleJarPath());\n```",
